body.description: Meet the one wipe for everything. Use Pampers Multi-Use Wipes for messes on body, face, surfaces and more. Multi-Use Wipes are hypoallergenic, and free of any alcohol, parabens, and latex*. They are clinically proven mild and dermatologically tested, too. Our Clean Breeze scent wipes have a delightfully clean and refreshing scent for an enjoyable clean. Our convenient 1-Wipe pop-top is designed to dispense one wipe at a time, so you only get what you need to tackle the mess at-hand. From Pampers, the #1 pediatrician recommended brand. Treat yourself & your little one to a fresh experience with Pampers Multi-Use baby wipes. Wherever your little one leaves a mess, Multi-Use Wipes are a sure bet to clean.

manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: On Hand, for Paws Put a pack near your pup’s food dish, snacks or wherever you keep their leash between walks. On the Job Keep a pack at your desk or other workspace to wipe down your surfaces and wipe up those coffee spills. The Workout Wipe Throw a pack in your gym bag or locker to wipe down equipment or freshen up post-workout. Bathroom Must Perfect for hands and faces—keep a pack of Expressions on the counter or under the sink. Laundry Room Fresh Store a pack in your laundry room or mudroom to keep your space clean and fresh. On the Go Toss a pack in your glove box or console for quick cleanups on the road.

What can these wipes be used for? Pampers Expressions Multi-Use Wipes can be used on body, face, messes, surfaces and more! They are gentle enough for faces, yet durable enough to take on tough messes. Are Pampers wipes safe for my baby? Yes! Babies' health and safety are our first priority at Pampers with our hypoallergenic products that are free of parabens and latex.* (*Natural Rubber) Our wipes are safe and are thoroughly tested to make sure they are safe for your baby. Are these wipes flushable? No. Our wipes are not designed to be flushed. Do Expressions wipes come with a pop-top? Yes! Pampers Expressions wipes are available with a pop-top that features a one-wipe dispensing lid, so you only get the wipes you need. What scents are Pampers Expressions Multi-Use Wipes available in? Expressions wipes are available in three varieties—Fragrance Free, Botanical Rain and Fresh Bloom. Our Botanical Rain scent is fresh and dewy and our Fresh Bloom scent is light, floral, fresh and fragrant.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 15, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Not Just for Babies...
reviews.reviewText: When my children were still little, we discovered that their wipes were handy for a dozen things besides diapers; so we've always kept a package or two of wipes around. They're cheaper than typical brand-name cleaning wipes, yet they do just as good a job on everything (except actual disinfecting). We also use them for personal/beauty wipes, for the same reason - they work fine and are FAR cheaper. Removing makeup/facial cleansing, freshening up, cooling off sweaty brows on hot summer days, wiping down sticky hands/faces ... extremely versatile.Normally I just buy whatever is on sale, but I was putting in a big Amazon order last week and added these in since we needed them. I am HOOKED! First of all, they SMELL. SO. GOOD. I can't even describe it, except that it's a fresh, sweet scent. If food smelled this good we'd be in trouble. Yet it's not overwhelming - just a ghost of it hovers around the skin after use.They also have castor oil in them, which is one of my most beloved go-to ingredients for everything. Because of the castor oil, the skin doesn't come out dry or irritated after use. The wipes just glide across, and skin feels like it's been cleansed and moisturized/lotioned without needing a second step. And did I mention it smells great?I highly recommend these. As a part-time esthetician, I teach simplicity in routines: find the most uncomplicated system, with the least (and least complex) products, that will work for you. I've never used big collections of products, just a simple basic cleanser followed with moisturizer (for me almost always one or two EOs with a coconut oil base, which I mix myself based on what mood my skin is in). These wipes are a fantastic way to remove makeup completely and/or cleanse your face. I'll be 50 in October, and my skin hasn't changed substantially in the past 10-15 years, so it must be working to some extent!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 9, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Great product! could use some improvement
reviews.reviewText: First and foremost, one of the standout features of Pampers Multi Use Baby Wipes is its gentle, fragrance-free formula. This aspect is particularly appealing for parents who prioritize minimizing exposure to potential irritants for their little ones. The mild scent, or rather the absence thereof, is a definite plus, especially for babies with sensitive skin or those prone to allergies. It provides peace of mind, knowing that the wipes are less likely to cause any adverse reactions.However, the experience of using these wipes is not without its nuances. One notable observation is the thinness of the wipes. While they effectively serve their purpose in terms of cleanliness, their thinness can sometimes lead to challenges during use. The tendency for the wipes to stick together can be a minor inconvenience, especially when trying to extract them quickly during diaper changes or other baby care tasks. This issue could potentially be addressed with slight improvements in the manufacturing process to enhance the structural integrity of the wipes.That being said, despite the thinness and occasional sticking together of the wipes, their overall performance remains satisfactory. They effectively clean and soothe delicate skin without causing irritation, which is paramount in any baby care product. Additionally, the packaging is convenient and user-friendly, featuring a resealable flap that helps maintain moisture and freshness.In conclusion, Pampers Multi Use Baby Wipes, Fragrance-Free, presents itself as a reliable option for parents seeking a gentle and fragrance-free solution for their baby's daily care needs. While the thinness and occasional sticking together of the wipes may pose minor inconveniences, the product's cleaning efficacy and skin-friendly formula outweigh these drawbacks. With a few refinements, such as enhancing the thickness and texture of the wipes, Pampers could further solidify its position as a trusted name in baby care essentials. Overall, I would recommend these wipes to parents looking for a gentle and fragrance-free option for their little one's hygiene routine.
